Microfluidics
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In preparation for future biosensing experiments, investigations regarding
 the fabrication and interfacing of microfluidic devices were carried out.
 These devices allow a very small volume of a fluid or gas introduced into
 the SPR sensor.
 In addition to its convenience, the small volumes employed work to reduce
 noise due to thermal fluctuations and diffusion.
 The microfluidics are fabricated by pouring a curable polymer over a planar
 mold containing raised features.
 When the cured polymer is removed and adhered to another surface, the raised
 features become small channels in which a target can flow.
\end_layout

