\begin_layout Standard
Adhering the finished device to the prism can be done in several ways.
 PDMS readily bonds to glass through plasma activated bonding, but this
 has the potential to oxidize a metal (silver) surface.
 If only a small amount of metal has been deposited on the prism, it may
 be protected from oxidization using a small piece of cured PDMS.
 It was also found that if the flow rate through the microfluidics is small
 enough, surface attraction alone between the PDMS and glass is enough to
 prevent leakage.
\end_layout

